cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper primarily focuses on the security and privacy implications of Certificate Transparency (CT) on the internet ecosystem. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the evolution of CT and its impact on website support, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper explores the use of CT logs for identifying targets for scanning campaigns, which relates to the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper presents a methodology for learning and validating new subdomains, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
